main event: A report of a sighting of one round white object moving from 030 degrees azimuth to 315 degrees over a 40-minute period.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 40 minutes,The object appeared round and white, comparable to the size of a star at arm's length,The object moved to the northwest and faded at the horizon, The observation was conducted at 0520 local time, and the report suggests the sighting was likely an aircraft.
